lyrics:
[Intro]
(Baby, I'm yours, yours, yours)
(Baby, I'm yours, yours, yours)

[Verse 1]
I know that you love me
Darling, you don't have to say it
You know you can trust me
It's okay, it's complicated

[Pre-Chorus]
Nervous, trip over my words
You're so pretty it hurts

[Chorus]
Baby, I'm yours
Baby, I'm yours
Baby, I'm yours
I need something more
I'll pray to the Lord
That baby, I'm yours

[Verse 2]
Is it too late to see you?
I love the view of your headlights
Wanna get to know you (Know you)
Brought you to my house for the night

[Pre-Chorus]
Nervous, trip over my words
You're so pretty it hurts

[Chorus]
Baby, I'm yours
Baby, I'm yours
Baby, I'm yours
I need something more
I'll pray to the Lord
That baby, I'm yours

[Bridge]
We're gettin' closer, inches away
Lose composure, favorite mistake
Friendship's over, won't be the same
(Baby, I'm yours, yours, yours)
(Baby, I'm yours, yours, yours)
(I need something morе, more, more)
(But baby, I'm yours)

[Chorus]
Baby, I'm yours
Baby, I'm yours
Baby, I'm yours
I need something morе
I'll pray to the Lord
That baby, I'm yours
imageDescription: An image of two intertwined hands, one slightly trembling, representing nervousness and vulnerability. In the background, there are car headlights shining through a window, symbolizing late-night encounters and the anticipation of getting closer. The simplicity of the image captures the longing and desire expressed in the song.
